headline.main: CATHOLIC CENTER OPENS TOMORROW; Sturgis Mansion at 17 East 51st St. to Be Available to Men in Armed Services

lead_paragraph: The mansion at 17 East Fifty-first Street, built in 1909 by the late Frank Knight Sturgis at a cost of $1,000,000 and recently acquired by Archbishop Francis J. Spellman for men in the military services and defense industries will be opened formally tomorrow.
